    "body": "Fixes #30102.\n\nThis updates the signet miner to retry block construction when `bitcoin-util grind` exhausts the nonce search space for a candidate block header. When the grinder fails specifically with `Could not satisfy difficulty target`, the miner advances the block time and tries again, while preserving the existing failure behavior for other grind errors.\n\nThe functional test now wraps `bitcoin-util grind` with a helper that fails the first attempt using the target-exhaustion message, then delegates to the real grinder. This exercises the retry path without requiring a long-running high-difficulty signet chain.\n\nTested with:\n\n```\npython3 -m py_compile contrib/signet/miner test/functional/tool_signet_miner.py\ngit diff --check origin/master..HEAD\nconda-build-env/bin/ninja -C build-clang22-clean bitcoind bitcoin-cli bitcoin-util\nPATH=$PWD/conda-build-env/bin:$PATH DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=$PWD/conda-build-env/lib HOME=$PWD/.conda-home CONDA_NUMBER_CHANNEL_NOTICES=0 CONDA_NO_PLUGINS=true CONDA_PKGS_DIRS=$PWD/.conda-pkgs XDG_CACHE_HOME=$PWD/.cache conda-build-env/bin/python build-clang22-clean/test/functional/test_runner.py --jobs=1 tool_signet_miner.py\n```",
